---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import "../../styles/globals.css";
import { Header } from "../../components/Header";
import InnerPageCTA from "../../components/InnerPageCTA.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

const b = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout
  title="Introducing the parcelLab App Store: The Solution That Unifies Your Returns Tech Stack - parcelLab"
  description="Discover the parcelLab App Store -- a central hub to discover, activate, and optimize returns solutions with plug-and-play integrations and AI agents."
>
  <Header client:load />
  <main>
    <!-- Article Header -->
    <section class="section-generous">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[1440px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px]">
          <a href={`${b}/blog/`} class="group mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-sm font-medium text-[var(--ink-muted)] transition-colors hover:text-[#3D3AD3]">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="transition-transform group-hover:-translate-x-0.5"><path d="M19 12H5"/><path d="m12 19-7-7 7-7"/></svg>
            Back to blog
          </a>
          <span class="mb-4 inline-block rounded-full bg-[#3D3AD3]/10 px-3 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-[#3D3AD3]">Returns</span>
          <h1 class="text-display text-[var(--ink)]">Introducing the parcelLab App Store: The Solution That Unifies Your Returns Tech Stack</h1>
          <div class="mt-6 flex items-center gap-4 text-sm text-[var(--ink-muted)]">
            <span>By <strong class="font-medium text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Vansh Kukreja</strong></span>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <time datetime="2025-07-14">July 14, 2025</time>
            <span class="h-1 w-1 rounded-full bg-[var(--ink-muted)]"></span>
            <span>4 min read</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Article Body -->
    <section class="pb-16 md:pb-24">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-[800px] px-6 md:px-12">
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed text-lg">
          Returns shouldn't be this hard. Yet too many retailers face tangled systems with disconnected tools rather than streamlined processes. The parcelLab App Store changes that -- a central hub to discover, activate, and optimize returns solutions within a unified platform.
        </p>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">The Problem</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          Retailers today wrestle with a familiar set of challenges in their returns operations:
        </p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#F4373D" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><path d="M18 6 6 18"/><path d="m6 6 12 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Inflexible, outdated returns systems lacking customization capabilities</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#F4373D" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><path d="M18 6 6 18"/><path d="m6 6 12 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Extended development timelines for implementing new features</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#F4373D" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><path d="M18 6 6 18"/><path d="m6 6 12 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Inconsistent customer communications and visibility gaps</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="#F4373D" stroke-width="2.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" class="mt-0.5 shrink-0"><path d="M18 6 6 18"/><path d="m6 6 12 12"/></svg>
            <span class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)]">Absence of automation or intelligence for learning from returns data</span>
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">The Power to Move Faster (and Smarter)</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          The App Store offers plug-and-play integrations with industry partners including Happy Returns, Metapack, ReBound, and Global-e. It promises flexibility without requiring technology stack overhauls.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-6 space-y-6">
          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">Returns Recipes</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              Pre-configured templates addressing real-world challenges like feedback capture automation and high-return customer reduction.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="rounded-xl border border-[var(--line)] bg-[var(--surface-raised)] p-6">
            <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--ink)]">AI Agents</h3>
            <p class="mt-2 text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
              The Return Save Agent offers personalized incentives to discourage returns, while the Returns Forecast AI predicts volume spikes for warehouse planning.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <h2 class="text-heading text-[var(--ink)] mt-12 mb-4">What This Means for Your Business</h2>
        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          The App Store delivers complete visibility, operational control, and process flexibility without IT dependency or customer experience compromise. It's designed to help retailers move at the speed of their business, not their backlog.
        </p>

        <div class="my-12 border-t border-[var(--line)]"></div>

        <p class="text-[var(--ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          The parcelLab App Store represents a fundamental shift in how retailers manage returns -- from fragmented tools to a unified, intelligent platform that grows with your business.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <InnerPageCTA />
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
